nd molecular mechanisms within living cells. It focuses on DNA replication, transcription, protein synthesis, and gene expression regulation.", "Nanotechnology is the manipulation of matter at the atomic and molecular scale, typically between 1 and 100 nanometers. It has applications in medicine, electronics, energy storage, and materials science."], "scores": [0.8159031770586518, 0.6716685834350347, 0.5630941091931035, 0.5425969199764462, 0.5395954132159585], "model_name": "bge-base", "document_ids": ["Robotics", "Cybernetics", "Neuroscience", "Molecular Biology", "Nanotechnology"]}}